  "title": "Pilgrim's Progress §373: HOPE.",
  "body": "HOPE. I know something of this myself; for, before I knew myself, it was so with me. CHR. Well, we will leave, at this time, our neighbour Ignorance by himself, and fall upon another profitable question. HOPE. With all my heart, but you shall still begin. CHR. Well then, did you not know, about ten years ago, one Temporary in your parts, who was a forward man in religion then? HOPE. Know him! yes, he dwelt in Graceless, a town about two miles off of Honesty, and he dwelt next door to one Turnback.",
